docs.abstract: Thousands of Americans move to New York each year, many of them seeking a fresh start. Even a pandemic couldn’t totally stop that.
docs.snippet: Thousands of Americans move to New York each year, many of them seeking a fresh start. Even a pandemic couldn’t totally stop that.
docs.lead_paragraph: Victoria Gruenert went through a sudden, ugly breakup this past spring, so she did what many 20-somethings have done before her: She picked up her things and moved to New York City, eager for a fresh start. But the city she had pictured in her head — a high-paced office life, a jam-packed social calendar, the bustling Manhattan she’d seen on TV — was gone.

headline.main: Is N.Y.C. ‘Over’? These Brand-New New Yorkers Don’t Think So
headline.print_headline: Feeling Drawn to New York in Spite of It All, Newcomers Say Hello to All That
